Interesting to see that they don&#x27;t shy away from using goto in their code.<p><a href="http://roslyn.codeplex.com/SourceControl/latest#Src/Compilers/CSharp/Source/Parser/Lexer.cs" rel="nofollow">http://roslyn.codeplex.com/SourceControl/latest#Src/Compiler...</a><p>Something I&#x27;ve just learned from looking at the code is you can jump between cases in a switch statement :<p><pre><code>    switch (a) {
       case &#x27;1&#x27;:
         ...
       case &#x27;2&#x27;:
         goto case &#x27;1&#x27;;
    }
 </code></pre>
Never realised you could do that.
